## Absolute rules — never break these regardless of mode
1. Never change function signatures in lib/api.ts — only swap implementations inside mock blocks
2. Never change visual design of HTML files in frontend/design/ — they are the visual reference
3. Adapt HTML designs to match actual system logic — if the HTML shows 6 pipeline stages
   but the system only has 4, use 4. HTML is visual reference, not spec.
4. S_final = (S_screen × 0.40) + (S_interview × 0.60) — formula locked
5. Screening threshold = 55/100 — never change
6. Every status change writes to audit trail (in mock: Supabase audit_log table)
7. Keep all files under 300 lines — split if longer
8. TypeScript strict mode always — no `any` types

